Restaurant Analogy
Suppose kitchen is overloaded.
Manager stops accepting new orders temporarily.
Why?
	• Prevent complete collapse 
	• Allow recovery 
	• Protect staff 
This is exactly what a circuit breaker does.

Interview Questions
Q1. Why is circuit breaker needed?
To prevent cascading failures and improve resilience.

Q2. What are the states of circuit breaker?
	• Closed 
	• Open 
	• Half-Open 

Q3. Difference between Retry and Circuit Breaker?
Retry retries requests.
Circuit breaker blocks requests.

Q4. What is fallback?
Alternative response when service fails.
Example:

“Service temporarily unavailable.”

Best Practices
1. Use with Retry Carefully
Too many retries can overload system.

2. Configure Proper Thresholds
Monitor production traffic.

3. Always Add Monitoring
Use:
	• Grafana 
	• Kibana 

4. Add Meaningful Fallbacks
Never show technical errors to users.

