If Payment Service fails:

Circuit Opens
↓
Fallback Response Returned

Final Summary
Circuit Breaker is one of the most important resiliency patterns in distributed systems.
It:
	• prevents cascading failures, 
	• protects resources, 
	• improves stability, 
	• helps systems recover gracefully. 
Modern microservices heavily rely on circuit breakers for high availability and fault tolerance.
